The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Greg will play a major role: More

Vadodara: Welcoming the appointment of Greg Chappell as new Indian cricket coach, selection committee chairman Kiran More said it would help the national team to build up its strength for the World Cup to be played in 2007. 

It is a good choice. He is an outstanding batsman of his times and would play a major role in bringing out talents of the Indian players, More said. 

The chief selector said the Australian had a vision and that would help Indian team reach top of the world. 

Chappell has a vision for Indian cricket. His appointment will help take the team to the top of world cricket. 

More also said he would prefer to consult the coach before selecting the team. 

Former Indian coach and Test batsman Aunshuman Gaekwad said Chappell was an experienced player and will help the Indian team to perform better. (PTI) 




